---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import SpecSection from "../components/SpecSection.astro";
---
<Layout
  title="TermCoder — study mode (TermExplorer)"
  description="TermExplorer is TermCoder's built-in study tutor: spaced-repetition flashcards, quizzes, and worked homework — the same engine, pointed at learning."
  active="study.html"
>
  <SpecSection gutter="//">
    <div class="t">
      <div class="mono-eyebrow"><span class="slash">//</span> TERMEXPLORER</div>
      <h2>A tutor is built in.</h2>
      <p class="lead">The same engine, pointed at studying instead of shipping. Switch to the
        <code>termexplorer/auto</code> model and the coding agent becomes a patient tutor — explaining,
        quizzing, and building flashcards from whatever you are learning.</p>
      <div class="row-2">
        <a class="btn-2 go" href="download.html">Download the app</a>
        <a class="btn-2" href="install.html">Install the CLI</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="a">
      <div class="deck">
        <div class="card-f">
          <div class="kicker">Flashcard · 1 of 8</div>
          <p class="q">What does the Krebs cycle produce for the electron transport chain?</p>
          <div class="meta"><span>space to flip</span><span class="streak">streak: 4 days</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </SpecSection>

  <SpecSection gutter="01" rev>
    <div class="t">
      <div class="num-head"><span class="nn">01</span><span class="lbl">ONE MODEL CHANGE</span></div>
      <h2>From coder to tutor.</h2>
      <p>Open the model picker and choose <code>termexplorer/auto</code>. Same keys, same free tier, same
        folder — the tone and the tools shift to teaching. Ask a question, paste a problem, or point it at
        your notes.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="a">
      <div class="snip">
        <div class="sbar"><span>termexplorer</span></div>
        <pre><span class="in">&#10095;</span> /model termexplorer/auto
<span class="out">&#10003;</span> switched to study mode
<span class="in">&#10095;</span> explain the krebs cycle, then quiz me
<span class="out">&#10003;</span> made 8 flashcards</pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </SpecSection>

  <SpecSection gutter="02">
    <div class="t">
      <div class="num-head"><span class="nn">02</span><span class="lbl">SPACED REPETITION</span></div>
      <h2>Cards come back at the right time.</h2>
      <p>Flashcards go into decks and resurface on a spaced-repetition schedule — recall one easily and it
        waits longer; miss it and it returns soon. A streak keeps you honest across the week.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="a">
      <div class="snip">
        <div class="sbar"><span>/review</span></div>
        <pre><span class="in">&#10095;</span> /review
  <span class="k">3/8 &#183; due today</span>
  <span class="c">easy &#8594; +4 days</span>
  <span class="c">again &#8594; +10 min</span>
  streak: <span class="out">4 days</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </SpecSection>

  <SpecSection gutter="03" rev>
    <div class="t">
      <div class="num-head"><span class="nn">03</span><span class="lbl">NOT JUST CODERS</span></div>
      <h2>Bring it to your next study session.</h2>
      <p>No terminal experience needed. Install once, pick the study model, and type your question in
        plain language — history, biology, math, a language. In the desktop app the decks live under the
        Study tab, one click away.</p>
      <div class="row-2"><a class="btn-2" href="docs.html">Read the docs</a></div>
    </div>
    <div class="a">
      <div class="deck">
        <div class="card-f">
          <div class="kicker">Deck · World History</div>
          <p class="q">Which treaty ended the Thirty Years' War, and in what year?</p>
          <div class="meta"><span>space to flip</span><span class="streak">12 cards</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </SpecSection>
</Layout>
